ALSO INCLUDED INSIDE THE SHIELD IS A DOUGLAS FIR TREE, AND OREGON PIONEER AND SIX OLYMPIC RINGS SUSPENDED FROM A ROPE ON EITHER SIDE OF THE CREST BOARDER. AT THE BOTTOM OF THE CREST ON EITHER SIDE OF THE TORCH BASE IS THE YEAR 1954. PROJECTING DOWNWARD FROM THE BOTTOM OF THE CREST IS THE HILT OF A DAGGER. THE DAGGER IS INTERTWINED WITH A SCROLL THAT SAYS "SOUTH SALEM". ON THE RIGHT EXTERIOR SIDE OF THE CREST ARE TWO RED ROSES OUTLINED IN SILVER. THE PORTLAND OREGON FIRE AND RESCUE LOGO HAS THE SHAPE OF A TRADITIONAL EIGHT-POINTED, FOUR ARMED FLORIAN CROSS, NAMED FOR THE PATRON SAINT OF FIREFIGHTERS. IN THE CENTER OF THE SHIELD IS A RED ROSE WITH THREE SETS OF GREEN LEAVES IN HONOR OF PORTLAND'S IDENTITY AS THE CITY OF ROSES.  THE ROSE IS BACKED WITH A GRAY OR SILVER CIRCLE FRAMED BY A GOLD RING. AT THE BOTTOM OF THE RING IT SAYS "EST. 1883". THE ARMS OF THE CROSS ARE OUTLINED IN THE SAME GOLD COLOR AND FILLED IN WITH BLACK.  INSIDE THE TOP ARM ARE THE WORDS "PORTLAND FIRE" IN GOLD. INSIDE THE RIGHT ARM IS A GOLD STAR OF LIFE, A SIX-ARMED STAR THAT INCLUDES THE STAFF OF ASCLEPIUS, A SERPENT-ENTWINED ROD USED BY A GREEK GOD ASSOCIATED WITH HEALING. THE STAR OF LIFE IS THE UNIVERSAL SYMBOL OF EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES. INSIDE THE BOTTOM ARM OF THE CROSS IS THE WORD "RESCUE" IN GOLD, AND INSIDE THE LEFT ARM IS THE IMAGE OF A GOLD FIRE HYDRANT. BETWEEN EACH OF THE ARMS THERE ARE POINTED GOLD BARS THAT END JUST BEFORE THE ARMS OF THE CROSS. TOGETHER THE FOUR LINES GIVE THE APPEARANCE OF A SQUARE SENT BEHIND THE CROSS.
